{
  "texts": [
    "However, electronic theft has increased, where hackers steal card details to dispossess cardholders of their money -causing considerable monetary losses for financial institutions and cardholders [17].",
    "The rise in fraud cases has raised concerns, making fraud detection a crucial and urgent task for businesses.",
    "Cyber-fraud can be grouped into the following classes: (a) the outright theft of credit cards, (b) the theft of confidential card details, often acquired via a variety of means, and (c) instances where card detail(s) is surreptitiously entered during an online transaction (without a cardholder's consent) -and leads to fraud [18], [19].",
    "The loss in cost associated with card fraud has since become staggering, with the payment card industry consequently incurring losses in billions of dollars annually.",
    "Thus, banks must remain committed to continued improvements in their fraud detection systems."
  ]
}